Most people do not know Sign language and interpreters are very difficult to come by we have come up with a real time method 
using neural networks for fingerspelling based american sign language.
In this method, the hand is first passed through a filter 
and after the filter is applied the hand is passed through a classifier
which predicts the class of the hand gestures. This method provides 98.00 % accuracy for the 26 letters of the alphabet.
